Paris Saint-Germain are insisting on Vinicius Jr. being included in any Real Madrid deal for Neymar. AS reports that the Ligue 1 champions will not do a deal without Vinicius. PSG have been interested in the Madrid forward for some time, even before the arrival of Leonardo as sporting director They have now asked for the teenage Brazilian three times and were rejected by the Spanish side. Neymar is set to feature in any game for PSG this season. However, both clubs have until September 2, to sort out an agreement. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.